flowRoot.flowPara: Only retain regulons with TGs that are significantly enriched for the TF motif
Only retain TGs with the TF motif
Only retain regulons that are enriched for marker genes (= DEGs) of a cluster
Only retain TGs that are marker genes for a cluster
Only retain a TF when it is expressed in X% of cells of a cluster
Calculate network statistics and functional (GO) enrichment
Option: run without calculating GO enrichment, in which case only the Std Borda ranking procedure can be used
Calculate Borda ranking using the Std or Ref procedure
Option: provide a list of GO terms of interest to run the Ref procedure, otherwise the Std procedure is used
Std (standard) procedure: unweighted Borda counts based on out-degree, closeness, betweenness and cluster specificity (marker gene enrichment)
Ref (reference) procedure: weighted Borda counts using R50 of TFs of interest as reference, based on the same metrics as for Std + functional (GO) enrichment
